narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Physical Oceanography: circulation patterns, effects on climate, equation of state of seawater, physical theories of ocean circulation, basic wave theory
Great introduction to Oceanography and the math and physics behind how the ocean works. Very quantitative but in a good way.
A broad introduction to physical oceanography, both conceptual and quantitative understanding of ocean characteristics and dynamics.
I learned about specific topics in oceanography and got a general overview of different areas of study within the field.
I learned all about the idea of physical oceanography and basics to many topics in the broad subject.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Not very engaging TA held office hours before every pset and exam which was very nice Material was well organized

The equations of motion really pulled everything together and I think it would be helpful to introduce them earlier in the course. After understanding them, things like geostrophy and the hydrostatic balance become easier to understand and use.

This course does a good job of covering basic topics in oceanography and the types of problems that can be solved by the fundamental laws in each area. The course material was generally interesting but sometimes felt slightly out of date. I wish some newer research had been introduced more often. The lectures could also be slightly faster paced and more engaging.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yep! Interesting material, great intro to practical application of math and physics.
A very interesting class as long as you have the math/physics background for it. Professor Fedorov is an excellent professor.
I would recommend this course to another student if they want an introduction to oceanography.
